      "review_summary": "The PR adds provider-scoped `inline-api-key:<provider>` cooldown state for inline provider API keys, gates those credentials in auth resolution/provider availability, preserves the new usage state, and adds regression coverage.\n\nPR surface: Source +298, Tests +472. Total +770 across 14 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. Source inspection on current main shows inline provider API keys resolve without a `profileId`, provider availability accepts config/env inline keys before cooldown checks, and auth failure marking returns when no profile id exists.",
